cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance of data-parallel workloads in resource-constrained environments and proposes a solution for cluster scheduling. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the memory requirements and performance of specific data-parallel tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a solution for optimizing cluster scheduling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as some of the data-parallel tasks mentioned in the paper, such as PageRank, are commonly used in machine learning applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the memory requirements and performance of tasks in various data-parallel frameworks.
